'''Level 300''' is the '''301<sup>st</sup>''' level of '''[[The Backrooms]]''' and is between '''[[Level 299]]''' and '''[[Level 301]]'''.
==<span style="font-size:30px;">'''Description'''</span>==
{{Blurimage Border|text-color=white|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=null|file=Mağara.jpg|𝚏𝚒𝚐=1.0|hovertext=Maden|caption=A photograph of '''Level 300'''.|width=320px}}
'''Level 300''' is a seemingly endless mine system that consists of randomly placed thin tunnels that are supported with a weak wooden skeleton to prevent the tunnels from collapsing. The tunnels lack any kind of order in their placement, to the point where one could encounter tunnels that are not clipped into each other. The tunnels usually lack any light, so bringing a light source is mandatory when entering '''Level 300'''.

Cartways are a common sight on this level and can be found in most tunnels alongside a cart. A thing that should be noted is that the cartways may lead the wanderers to dead ends, pits, and other types of obstacles that may pose a risk to one's life. Recent studies have shown that the level is rich in terms of resources such as boron, gold, copper, and other types of valuable metals.
{{Blurimage Border|text-color=white|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=null|file=300.png|𝚏𝚒𝚐=2.0|hovertext=Caves|caption=Another B&W image of '''Level 300'''.|width=320px}}
The level is covered in a gas that consists heavily of '''CO2''' and other types of neurological gases. Long-term exposure to this gas may cause neurological symptoms such as muscle spasms, balance problems, delirium, and psychosis.

The main threat to one's life in this level isn't the entities themselves, but the environment itself. The wooden skeletons that are supposed to prevent the tunnels from collapsing may break apart easily and cause the tunnels to collapse on their own.

That's why being careful and cautious is vital for survival in this level, due to the chaotic environment that one will find themself in after entering this level. Rarely, large pits filled with water or small rivers could be spotted in this level. The water within those structures has a PH rate of 13,5 which makes it unsafe for consumption. The reason behind the high PH rate of the water is thought to be caused by the minerals that are locked inside the rocks getting exposed and mixed with water due to the erosion of the rock surfaces.
{{Blurimage Border|text-color=white|border-color=white|box-shadow-color=null|file=300old.png|𝚏𝚒𝚐=3.0|hovertext=Oldness|caption=The oldest photograph of '''Level 300'''.|width=320px}}
The general temperature within the level ranges between 10-15°C, depending on the location. A general fall in temperature within the level has been spotted as one goes deeper, down to the point where liquids and water couldn't exist.

Recent studies have shown that the deeper the wanderers go, the more chaotic the level gets. A general increase in the risk of the tunnels collapsing has been spotted as one goes deeper. That's why staying close to the surface as much as possible is vital for survival in this level.

==<span style="font-size:30px;">Entities</span>==
Physical entities are a rare but existent sighting in this level. The most common entities include '''[[Entity 3|Smilers]]''', '''[[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]]''', '''[[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]]''', and '''[[Entity 9|Facelings]]'''. As mentioned above, the main threat to human life in '''Level 300''' isn't the entities, but the environment itself.

There IS a level-exclusive entity in '''Level 300''' that appears to look like a minecart that chases the wanderer and tries to run the wanderer over. Getting run over will kill the wanderer or send them to '''[[The Broken]]'''. Not much information is known about this level-exclusive entity, due to it rarely appearing in '''Level 300'''.
==<span style="font-size:30px;">Colonies & Outposts</span>==
There are no known settled colonies and outposts on this level, most likely due to the chaotic environment. But it is thought that many nomadic groups and organizations wander around this level, which are usually aggressive on sight.

Multiple colonies have lived in the minecarts due to them being huge, but all have been extinct due to the minecarts falling off dead-ends. No remains of these minecarts have been found, and the entities can also fall off the dead-ends, including the minecart entity.
==<span style="font-size:30px;">Addendum</span>==
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Expedition Log: "Level 300"</span><br>
So.. I don't know where I am right now.

All I see is a claustrophobic cave filled with tracks and collapsing stone. I hear weird cave noises in my ears. It feels like liminality. There's some [[Hydrolitis Plague|weird water]] flooding the cave. I might need to get out quickly.

First, I'll wander around the place; maybe look for some supplies or an exit to get out of here before I encounter any entities. It's hard to breathe right now.

I've heard about this level; '''Level 300'''. It's a Class 3e, which isn't very good. [[Small Talk|I've been through worse]]. I miss my wife. 

Secondly, I'll find a colony to reside in so they can help me get better. I have quite some scars around me when that [[Entity 3|thing almost tore me up..]] Lastly, I'll-

Wait, I see something moving towards me..</div></span>
==<span style="font-size:30px;">Entrances & Exits</span>==
===<span style="font-size:20px;">Entrances</span>===
*Rarely, the roads within '''[[Level 9]]''' may lead one to tunnels that could eventually lead to this level.
*Falling into giant rocky holes in '''[[Level 301]]''' may lead one to this level.
*Entering a mineshaft on '''[[Level 991]]''' may lead to this level.
*A crack in '''[[Level 0]]'s''' walls will send one here.
*<!-- tribute to sherls -->Reading a book about '''Level 300''' in '''[[Level 123]]''' will send one here.
*'''[[Level 200]]'s''' caves could send one here.
*<!-- another tribue with arbi and sherls -->Entering a hidden cave in '''[[Level 96]]''' or '''[[Level 55]]''' will send one here.
===<span style="font-size:20px;">Exits</span>===
*Going through a door that resembles a fire exit may lead one to Level 3.
*It is rumored that one could randomly no-clip through the floor involuntarily and end up in '''[[Level 299]]''' or '''[[Level 39]]''', although this is unconfirmed.
